Over a while, changes in the environment, such as climate, weather, pollution, 
will have a more significant impact on the structures in different ways. Hence, 
continuous monitoring of the structures plays a vital role in order to have a 
predefined prediction of the structural damages that can be caused by the change 
in the environment. Structural health monitoring (SHM) is critical in 
determining the life expectancy of civil structures. The advancement of various 
